{
  "__inputs": [
    {
      "name": "DS_PROMETHEUS",
      "label": "Prometheus",
      "description": "",
      "type": "datasource",
      "pluginId": "prometheus",
      "pluginName": "Prometheus"
    },
    {
      "name": "DS_LOKI",
      "label": "Loki",
      "description": "",
      "type": "datasource",
      "pluginId": "loki",
      "pluginName": "Loki"
    }
  ],
  "__requires": [
    {
      "type": "datasource",
      "id": "prometheus",
      "name": "Prometheus",
      "version": "1.0.0"
    },
    {
      "type": "datasource",
      "id": "loki",
      "name": "Loki",
      "version": "1.0.0"
    }
  ],
  "annotations": {
    "list": []
  },
  "description": "UniFi AP health — 8.6.10 symptom watch. Story: is AP01-Trapkast (U7 Pro XGS, 8.6.10) misbehaving? Top section: per-AP Prometheus health (uptime, uplink speed, client counts, firmware). Middle: syslog activity (proxy for connectivity), error-level log rate, client connection events on AP01. Bottom: crash/reboot signals, WAN context. Data sources: Prometheus unifi-exporter (per-AP metrics) + Loki syslog streams.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "panels": [
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 20,
      "title": "AP Health — Prometheus Metrics",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: has any AP rebooted recently? Seconds since each AP last booted, from unifi_ap_uptime_seconds. Red threshold: < 86400s (24h) — the 8.6.10 crash/reboot regression signal. AP01 (U7 Pro XGS on 8.6.10) with a fresh uptime while others are days old = AP01 rebooted without a planned change.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 3600
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 21600
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 86400
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "s",
          "mappings": [],
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.hostname}"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 21,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "justifyMode": "auto",
        "orientation": "horizontal",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "auto"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "unifi_ap_uptime_seconds",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Uptime (unifi_ap_uptime_seconds)",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: is AP01's 10G uplink healthy? Speed in Mbps reported by the unifi-exporter (unifi_ap_uplink_speed_mbps). AP01 (U7 Pro XGS) should show 10000 Mbps on its SFP+ port. Red if < 1000 Mbps — below 1 Gbps means either a cable/port issue or the 8.6.10 speed-negotiation regression. Other APs at 1000 Mbps is normal (1G copper uplinks).",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 100
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 1000
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "Mbps",
          "mappings": [],
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.hostname}"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 22,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "justifyMode": "auto",
        "orientation": "horizontal",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "auto"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "unifi_ap_uplink_speed_mbps",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Uplink Speed (unifi_ap_uplink_speed_mbps)",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: are clients falling off any AP over time? The 8.6.10 regression shows as a gradual slope downward on AP01 while other APs stay flat. Stacked area by radio band (2g, 5g, 6g) per AP, from unifi_ap_clients{radio}. A sudden vertical drop on AP01 while syslog is still active = clients disassociating without AP reboot (the subtle regression pattern).",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 20,
            "gradientMode": "none",
            "showPoints": "never",
            "stacking": {
              "mode": "normal",
              "group": "A"
            }
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.hostname} / ${__field.labels.radio}"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 6
      },
      "id": 23,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull", "mean"],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "right"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "unifi_ap_clients",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}} / {{radio}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Clients per AP per Radio (unifi_ap_clients — 8.6.10 client-collapse signal)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: what firmware is each AP running right now? Uses the info-metric unifi_ap_firmware_info (always=1, version label carries the string). Pulled from Prometheus — canonical and queryable, no Loki label-parsing required. AP01 on 8.6.10+18869 is the regression subject.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "custom": {
            "displayMode": "auto",
            "inspect": false
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 14
      },
      "id": 24,
      "options": {
        "footer": {
          "enablePagination": false,
          "fields": "",
          "reducer": ["sum"],
          "show": false
        },
        "showHeader": true,
        "sortBy": [
          {
            "desc": false,
            "displayName": "Hostname"
          }
        ]
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "unifi_ap_firmware_info",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "refId": "A",
          "instant": true,
          "format": "table"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Firmware Version (unifi_ap_firmware_info)",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "excludeByName": {
              "Time": true,
              "Value": true,
              "__name__": true,
              "job": true,
              "instance": true
            },
            "renameByName": {
              "hostname": "AP Hostname",
              "mac": "MAC Address",
              "version": "Firmware Version"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "hostname": 0,
              "mac": 1,
              "version": 2
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "type": "table"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 19
      },
      "id": 10,
      "title": "AP Connectivity (Syslog Heartbeat)",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: which APs are alive right now? A bar/line showing log lines per AP per 5 min. An AP that goes silent = no syslog = likely offline or rebooting. AP01-Trapkast on 8.6.10 highlighted. Note: syslog silence >10 min is more reliable than the 5-min window — use this as a trend signal, not a strict up/down indicator.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 8,
            "gradientMode": "none",
            "showPoints": "never"
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.hostname}"
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byFrameRefID",
              "options": "AP01"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "red",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.lineWidth",
                "value": 3
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 16,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 20
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "right"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (hostname) (count_over_time({hostname=\"AP01-Trapkast\"}[$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "AP01-Trapkast (8.6.10)",
          "refId": "AP01"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (hostname) (count_over_time({hostname=~\"AP02-Stube|AP03-Slaapkamer|AP04-Zolder|AP06-Keuken\"}[$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "refId": "OtherAPs"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Syslog Activity (log lines / interval)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
      },
      "description": "Current syslog line count per AP in the last 5 minutes. Green = active. Red/orange = silent (possible reboot or network loss). AP01 (8.6.10) threshold: warn if 0 lines for >5 min during daytime.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 1
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 3
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "mappings": []
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 20
      },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "justifyMode": "auto",
        "orientation": "auto",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "auto"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (hostname) (count_over_time({hostname=~\"AP01-Trapkast|AP02-Stube|AP03-Slaapkamer|AP04-Zolder|AP06-Keuken\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Syslog Heartbeat (last 5 min)",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 27
      },
      "id": 11,
      "title": "8.6.10 Symptom Signals — AP01 Focus",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: are clients being rejected or dropping off AP01? Rate of AP-STA-CONNECTED events from hostapd on AP01-Trapkast per 5 min. The 8.6.10 symptom: clients stop associating after a few hours. A sustained drop to zero while the AP is still sending syslog = regression suspect.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "fixed",
            "fixedColor": "red"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 15,
            "gradientMode": "none",
            "showPoints": "auto"
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "displayName": "Client connects / 5m"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 28
      },
      "id": 3,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": ["mean", "lastNotNull"],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "single",
          "sort": "none"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(count_over_time({hostname=\"AP01-Trapkast\"} |= \"AP-STA-CONNECTED\" [$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "AP01 client connects",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(count_over_time({hostname=\"AP01-Trapkast\"} |= \"AP-STA-DISCONNECTED\" [$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "AP01 client disconnects",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP01 Client Connect / Disconnect Events (8.6.10 symptom)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: is AP01 crashing? Count of error-level syslog messages per AP per interval. A spike in AP01 errors = kernel panic, hostapd crash, or driver fault. 8.6.10 reported: hostapd crashes on 6 GHz and traffic drops on 10G port. Other APs shown for baseline comparison.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 1,
            "fillOpacity": 20,
            "gradientMode": "none",
            "showPoints": "never",
            "stacking": {
              "mode": "none"
            }
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.hostname}"
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byFrameRefID",
              "options": "AP01err"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "dark-red",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.lineWidth",
                "value": 3
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 28
      },
      "id": 4,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": ["sum", "max"],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(count_over_time({hostname=\"AP01-Trapkast\", level=\"err\"} [$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "AP01-Trapkast (8.6.10)",
          "refId": "AP01err"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (hostname) (count_over_time({hostname=~\"AP02-Stube|AP03-Slaapkamer|AP04-Zolder|AP06-Keuken\", level=\"err\"} [$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "refId": "OtherErr"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Error-Level Log Rate (crash / driver fault signals)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 35
      },
      "id": 12,
      "title": "Reboot & Crash Events",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: has any AP rebooted recently? Uses 'halt WUL state due to USW/UDM reboot' and crash payload messages as reboot proxies. A bar appearing = AP had an uplink reset or self-reboot event. AP01 bar in this time window without a planned change = regression suspect.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 80,
            "gradientMode": "none",
            "lineWidth": 1
          },
          "unit": "short",
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.hostname}"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 36
      },
      "id": 5,
      "options": {
        "fillOpacity": 80,
        "gradientMode": "none",
        "legend": {
          "calcs": ["sum"],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (hostname) (count_over_time({hostname=~\"AP01-Trapkast|AP02-Stube|AP03-Slaapkamer|AP04-Zolder|AP06-Keuken\"} |= \"halt WUL state\" [$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}} reboot proxy",
          "refId": "Reboot"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (hostname) (count_over_time({hostname=~\"AP01-Trapkast|AP02-Stube|AP03-Slaapkamer|AP04-Zolder|AP06-Keuken\"} |= \"crash.save_crash_payload\" [$__interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}} crash payload",
          "refId": "Crash"
        }
      ],
      "title": "AP Reboot & Crash Events (uplink-monitor + crash payload signals)",
      "type": "barchart"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: is the internet up and the UDM healthy? WAN rx/tx throughput and UDM gateway uptime from the minimal unifi-exporter (polls /stat/health every 60s). A gateway uptime reset = UDM reboot. Context for AP anomalies: if the UDM rebooted, AP disconnects are expected.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 5,
            "gradientMode": "none",
            "showPoints": "never"
          },
          "unit": "Bps",
          "displayName": "${__field.name}"
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "WAN RX"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "blue",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "WAN TX"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "orange",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 36
      },
      "id": 6,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull", "mean"],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "none"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "unifi_wan_rx_bytes_per_second",
          "legendFormat": "WAN RX",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "unifi_wan_tx_bytes_per_second",
          "legendFormat": "WAN TX",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "WAN Throughput (UDM /stat/health, 60s poll)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    }
  ],
  "refresh": "5m",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "tags": ["unifi", "ap", "wifi", "8.6.10"],
  "time": {
    "from": "now-6h",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "timepicker": {},
  "timezone": "browser",
  "title": "UniFi AP Health (8.6.10 Watch)",
  "uid": "unifi-ap-health",
  "version": 2
}
